CHOLERA - RUSSIA (DAGESTAN) (03)
********************************
A ProMED-mail post
<http://www.healthnet.org/programs/promed.html>
See Also
Cholera - Russia (Dagestan) 981020205738
Cholera - Russia (Dagestan) (02) 981102202053
Date: Tue, 3 Nov 1998 17:33:57 -0500 (EST)
Source: WER, 23 to 29 Oct 1998, Outbreak News
Via: Marianne Hopp <mhopp@students.wisc.edu>

During the first half of October, a small outbreak of cholera occurred in
the southern part of the Republic of Dagestan. Laboratory investigations
have identified _Vibrio cholerae_ serotype Ogawa biotype El Tor. The
outbreak may have been caused by contaminated water supplies.
